com.inqwell.any

Class InqAddress

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.inqwell.any.AbstractAny
      • com.inqwell.any.InqAddress
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Any, Serializable

    public class InqAddress
extends AbstractAny
    The address of an <inq>TM server and user process within it.

    An InqAddress represents a destination process in an inq server amongst a network of such servers. Using an address an originating inq process can make service requests in processes elsewhere in an inter-connected inq network without knowing exactly where that service will run. Addresses take the form 

    
   user@domain
    where domain represents the inq server and user the process within that server.

    Each server node has an address table it uses to determine whether the current server is the desired one or that the message must be forwarded. If the destination server has been reached then that server's user process list is consulted to determine the destination process.
